race.comment: Open race but sticking with MAXIMUS BON (4). Lightly raced gelding working back into fitness and should be ready to fire after two runs back. Coming back in trip slightly and might get beaten for early dash but should be winding up hard. GREAT FUEGO (11) turned in a solid debut when finishing fifth, working to the line well. Has upside and is worth following in. TIKKEN (7) is fitter for two runs back, the latest sitting on pace and boxing on well to finish runner-up. Ready to win and gets his chance. FONN POWER (2) resumed from a break on the tricky Mount Gambier track and got home well into seventh, beaten a couple of lengths. Fitter again and should relish the extra trip. ICARO (3 is a gelding by Needs Further out of Saigon Princess who makes his debut. Has had three jump-outs, two recently, and is worth watching closely for a betting move.
